Stuart John Wood (born 25 February 1957) is a Scottish musician, songwriter and producer best known as a guitarist for the 1970s band the Bay City Rollers.
In December 2019 Wood rescued Kruger, a 10-year-old black Labrador, which had gone missing in North Berwick, East Lothian.
